HEADWORD: Leitneria
<hw>Leitneria</hw> <pos>prop. n.</pos> <def>A genus of trees or shrubs
coextensive with the family <fam>Leitneriaceae</fam>, and including the
corkwood (<spn>Leitneria floridana</spn>).</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> family <fam>Leitneriaceae</fam>, corkwood
family.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

